   <text>
      <body>
         <pb facs="1866_05_11_Illies_Shanghai_von_Gildemeister_Yokohama_(Masch. Abschrift)_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>
            <hi rend="print">
               <seg rend="left">
                  <hi rend="underline">Abschrift</hi>
               </seg>
               <lb/>
               <seg rend="right">
                  <placeName ref="K00525">Yokohama</placeName>, <date when="1866-05-11">11.
                            Mai 1866</date>
               </seg>
               <lb/> Werther Herr <persName ref="K00018">Illies</persName> ! <lb/> In der
                    Hoffnung, dass dieser Brief Sie wohl<lb/> und munter in <placeName ref="K00503">Shanghai</placeName> antreffen wird ersuche ich Sie Ihre<lb/> Reise sofort
                    nach hier fortsetzen zu wollen, da Sie hier<lb/> zunächst genügend Arbeit
                    vorfinden werden.<lb/>
               <seg rend="right">Ihr ergebener<lb/>
                  <persName ref="K00011">M. H. Gildemeister</persName>
               </seg>
               <lb/> (Bem. <persName ref="K00018">C. I. sen.</persName>: damaliger Chef und
                    Theilhaber von <orgName type="firm" ref="K01004">L.<lb/>
                  <seg rend="right">Kniffler &amp; Co.)</seg>
               </orgName>
               <lb/> Adresse: <persName ref="K00018">Carl Illies</persName>
               <choice>
                  <abbr>Esq</abbr>
                  <expan>Esquire</expan>
               </choice>.<lb/> to be expected p. French Mail <choice>
                  <abbr>Str.</abbr>
                  <expan>Steamer</expan>
               </choice> from <placeName ref="K00511">Europe</placeName>
               <lb/>
               <seg rend="right">
                  <placeName ref="K00503">Shanghai</placeName>
               </seg>
               <lb/> Bem. <persName ref="K00018">Carl I.sen.</persName>: Anfang <date when="1866-06">Juni 1866</date> erhalten). </hi>
         </p>
         <pb facs="1866_05_11_Illies_Shanghai_von_Gildemeister_Yokohama_(Masch. Abschrift)_2.tif" n="2"/>
      </body>
   </text>
   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1866_05_11_Illies_Shanghai_von_Gildemeister_Yokohama_(Masch. Abschrift)_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>Copy<lb/>Yokohama, 11th May 1866<lb/>Dear Mr. Illies ! <lb/>In the hope that this
                letter is finding you fit and <lb/>well in Shanghai, I am entreating you to consider
                <lb/>continuing your journey here immediately as you will<lb/>find enough work to
                start with here. <lb/>Yours sincerely <lb/> M. H. Gildemeister<lb/>(Note: C. I.
                sen.: then boss and partner of L.<lb/>Kniffler &amp; Co.)<lb/> Adress: Carl Illies
                Esq.<lb/>to be expected per French Mail steamer from Europe<lb/>Shanghai<lb/>Note:
                Carl I.sen.: received early June1866). </p>
         <pb facs="1866_05_11_Illies_Shanghai_von_Gildemeister_Yokohama_(Masch. Abschrift)_1.tif" n="2"/>
      </body>
   </text>
